      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Complete List of Two-Letter Scrabble Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Two-letter words are the backbone of competitive Scrabble. They let you play parallel to existing words, hook onto tiles already on the board, and squeeze points from tight spaces that longer words simply cannot reach. Memorising this complete list is one of the single biggest improvements any player can make to their game. Below you'll find every valid two-letter word in SOWPODS — the international Scrabble dictionary — organised for easy reference.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Two-Letter Words Matter</h2>
      <p>In a standard Scrabble game, the board fills up quickly. By the mid-game, most available plays require forming at least one two-letter word as a crossword alongside your main word. Players who know all 127 valid two-letter words have a massive advantage — they see plays that others miss entirely.</p>
      <p>Two-letter words enable parallel plays (laying a word alongside an existing one, forming multiple two-letter crosswords simultaneously). A single parallel play can score 30-50+ points by hitting multiple premium squares at once. They also let you dump difficult tiles without wasting a turn exchanging.</p>
      <p>Our <a href="/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">free word finder</a> shows you all valid words from your tiles in realtime — including every two-letter option available.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Vowel-Starting Two-Letter Words</h2>
      <p>Words beginning with A, E, I, O, or U. These are especially useful because vowel-heavy racks are common, and knowing vowel starters helps you play through them efficiently.</p>

